Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium pink-brown; grey core; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp with [club] symbol.
Type series: KT121 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 91, 1. Names, Timasikrates, Anaxandrou.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0312)
